Supported commands:
    prepare_sources     Prepare sources
    generate_spec       Generate spec file
    build_rpm           Build rpm
    build_iso           Build iso

Prepare sources:
    In current directory
    1) Write file "module.config" with config template
    2) Create directory structure for rpm build
       .
       ├─── rpm
           ├── BUILD
           ├── BUILDROOT
           ├── RPMS
           ├── SOURCES
           ├── SPECS
           └── SRPMS
    3) Create directory "src" for module source code
    4) Create directory "patches" for patches

Generate Spec:
    Command need prapered module.config file
    Command will create new spec file based on module.config file
    1) Check if spec already exist, when yes write warning and continue
    2) Add patches from src/patches directory into spec
    3) Create spec in rpm/SPECS directory with values defined in config

Build rpm:
    3 stages command:
        Stage 1) Prepare source
            a) Generate module.files & makefile(when no present in user source)
            b) Pack source in src and write it into rpm/SOURCES
            c) Copy module.files & makefile & patch into rpm/SOURCES

        Stage 2) Generate build outputs for final rpm
            a) Copy patches
            b) Build module
            c) Generate greylist & module.symvers and write into rpm/SOURCES

        Stage 3) Build rpm
            # stage driven by specfile
            a) Build module
            b) Sign module (when it is supported by infrastructure)
            c) Run depmod
            d) Run find-requires, find-provides
            e) Write final rpm, srpm

Build ISO:
    1) Collect rpms/srpms for all arches
    2) Prepare iso filesystem
    3) Prepare repository
    4) Add rpms/srpms into repository
    5) Write repository into iso
